+# Character Art Prompts — Anime, 5-Tier Aesthetic Ladder
+
+The visual style IS the power ranking. Weakest → strongest:
+
+| Rank | Aesthetic Band | Rarity it rolls from | Feel |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| 1 | **Medieval European** | Common | grounded, muted, no glow |
+| 2 | **Xianxia Normal** | Uncommon | cultivation, silk, soft qi |
+| 3 | **Xianxia Horror** | Rare | corrupted cultivators, demonic qi |
+| 4 | **Victorian Normal** | Epic | gothic aristocrat occultists |
+| 5 | **Victorian Horror** | Legendary | eldritch reality-warping horror |
+
+Confirmed working in-game: a 10-pull gave Medieval (rank 1, ~146 ATK) → Xianxia Normal (rank 2, ~467) → Xianxia Horror (rank 3, ~985) → Victorian Normal (rank 4, ~1593). **Strength follows the ladder**, so the look genuinely signals power.
+
+---
+
+## SHARED BASE — prepend to EVERY prompt
+```
+anime style game character, isometric three-quarter top-down view, full body,
+centered, clean silhouette, transparent background, cel-shaded with crisp
+lineart, vibrant anime colors, cohesive RPG art style, 512px, no text, no border
+```
+
+---
+
+## TIER 1 — MEDIEVAL EUROPEAN (weakest)
+**Style tag:** `medieval European fantasy, practical worn armor, realistic medieval weapons, muted earthy palette, no magic glow`
+
+- **Spearman** — young anime knight-footman with a long steel spear and kite shield, chainmail under a tabard, brown and iron tones
+- **Swordsman** — anime squire swordsman in a guard stance, gambeson and partial plate, arming sword, slate and steel
+- **Archer** — anime medieval longbowman drawing a yew bow, hooded leather jerkin, quiver, forest green and tan
+- **Scout** — agile anime outrider crouched low, light traveling leathers, dagger and map case, dusty olive and brown
+- **Mercenary** — grizzled anime sellsword resting a broadsword on his shoulder, battered mismatched plate, weathered iron and rust
+- **Trapper** — rugged anime woodsman setting a snare, fur-trimmed cloak, ropes and traps at the belt, umber and grey
+
+## TIER 2 — XIANXIA NORMAL
+**Style tag:** `xianxia cultivation fantasy, flowing silk hanfu robes, serene, soft glowing qi energy, jade and gold palette`
+
+- **Herbalist** — gentle anime cultivator herbalist with a woven medicine basket, layered jade silk robes, faint green qi wisp, calm
+- **Mage** — anime qi-caster holding a glowing paper talisman, elegant violet-and-white robes, swirling soft purple energy
+- **Priest** — anime temple cultivator in prayer, white-and-jade vestments, prayer beads, gentle warm golden halo of light
+- **Sage** — elderly anime cultivation sage levitating cross-legged, long beard, flowing robes, orbiting glowing qi motes, jade-gold aura
+
+## TIER 3 — XIANXIA HORROR
+**Style tag:** `corrupted dark xianxia, tattered blood-stained robes, demonic crimson-black qi, ominous, glowing red eyes, eerie atmosphere`
+
+- **Assassin** — masked anime demonic-cultivator assassin in a low pose, tattered black wraps, twin blades dripping dark qi, crimson glowing eyes
+- **Shadow-Dancer** — sinister anime shadow cultivator mid-spin, twin curved daggers trailing black smoke, torn violet-black robes, malevolent red glow
+- **Beast-Master** — corrupted anime beast-tamer beside a shadowy demon-beast, bone-and-fur dark armor, pulsing crimson qi veins, menacing
+
+## TIER 4 — VICTORIAN NORMAL
+**Style tag:** `Victorian gothic, ornate 1800s aristocrat attire, tailcoats and corsetry, brass and lace details, candlelit muted jewel tones, occult elegance`
+
+- **Paladin** — anime Victorian holy-order knight, ornate brass-trimmed gothic plate over a long coat, blessed saber, faint silver-white glow, stern noble bearing
+- **Spellblade** — anime Victorian occult duelist, rune-etched rapier wreathed in pale arcane fire, embroidered tailcoat and gloves, cold blue energy
+- **Virtue** — anime Victorian inquisitor holding a glowing brass scale of judgment, ornate ivory-and-gold gothic dress-armor, ring of soft light, refined
+
+## TIER 5 — VICTORIAN HORROR (strongest)
+**Style tag:** `eldritch Victorian gothic horror, reality-bending, ornate decaying aristocrat attire fused with cosmic void, writhing tendrils, otherworldly glow, terrifying grandeur, heavy VFX`
+
+- **Seraph** — anime eldritch Victorian seraph, too many feathered wings and halos of burning eyes, gilded gothic vestments, blinding gold-white corrupted holy aura
+- **Cherub** — unsettling anime Victorian cherub, doll-like with multiple small wings and a fractured halo, lace-and-brass gown, eerie luminous blue glow
+- **Dominion** — imperious anime Victorian dominion wielding a radiant brass scepter, layered decaying robes, ring of floating halos, regal gold-and-black void light
+- **Archangel** — towering anime eldritch archangel in cracked gothic warplate, enormous spread wings of light and shadow, flaming greatsword, blinding corrupted corona
+- **Creator** — anime eldritch god-aristocrat weaving a small galaxy between gloved hands, robes of living starfield, crown of orbiting worlds, cosmic gold-violet radiance
+- **Void-God** — anime void-deity in a Victorian silhouette dissolving into writhing tendrils and stars, fractured porcelain mask, abyssal purple-black with void-light cracks
+- **Time-Weaver** — anime chrono-deity surrounded by floating brass clock gears and shattered time-shards, gothic robe shimmering with shifting hours, teal-bronze temporal glow
+- **Life-Bringer** — anime eldritch life-goddess in a decaying Victorian gown blooming with luminous unnatural flora and vines, halo of growing leaves, radiant emerald-gold energy
+- **Entropy** — anime entropy-god of decay in crumbling gothic finery dissolving into glowing ash and unraveling threads, cracked cosmic armor, ominous ember-orange and ash-grey aura
+
+---
+
+## Leonardo production tips
+- **Fix a seed per class** so you can regenerate a consistent version later.
+- **Generate at 512–1024px, downscale** to your 32–64px sprite size (downscaling sharpens; upscaling muddies).
+- For **Tier 5**, push `transparent background` + `centered, full body` hard — the heavy VFX otherwise bleeds to the canvas edge and breaks paper-doll layering.
+- Keep the **shared base** identical across all 18 so they read as one roster despite the wildly different eras.
+
+## Code/DB changes that back this (already built + tested)
+- `database/migrations/003_aesthetic_tiers.sql` — replaces the old 4 tiers (mortal/heroic/angelic/divine) with the 5 aesthetic bands + a `tier_rank` (1–5) for strength comparisons. Migrates existing rows, idempotent.
+- `server/api/heroes.ts` — updated so summoning assigns the correct band per class and scales stats by tier rank (×1, ×2.5, ×5, ×9, ×16). Verified: rarity → band → strength all line up.
+- Apply order: `001` → `002` → `003`.
