+# Hero Sprites — drop Leonardo PNGs here
+
+The game loads `assets/heroes/<slug>.png` per class. If a file is missing, the
+hero shows a colored placeholder card instead (no crash). So you can add art
+one tier at a time — present classes get their sprite automatically.
+
+## Filename = lowercased class name, spaces -> underscores, hyphens kept
+
+### TIER 1 — Medieval European  (you have art ✓)
+  spearman.png  swordsman.png  archer.png  scout.png  mercenary.png  trapper.png
+
+### TIER 2 — Xianxia Normal  (you have art ✓)
+  herbalist.png  mage.png  priest.png  sage.png
+
+### TIER 3 — Xianxia Horror  (you have art ✓)
+  assassin.png  shadow-dancer.png  beast-master.png
+
+### TIER 4 — Victorian Normal  (TODO — placeholder card shows until added)
+  paladin.png  spellblade.png  virtue.png
+
+### TIER 5 — Victorian Horror  (TODO — placeholder card shows until added)
+  seraph.png  cherub.png  dominion.png  archangel.png
+  creator.png  void-god.png  time-weaver.png  life-bringer.png  entropy.png
+
+## Notes
+- PNG with transparent background recommended (cards/portraits composite cleanly).
+- .jpg also works as a fallback if you didn't export PNG.
+- Any size; the game fits them into the card/portrait box automatically.
+- These are gitignored by default? No — commit them so the build copies them.
